*34	    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> strategy<br>
--------------<br>
<br>
sites:<br>
1) prancing pony<br>
doesn matter if i dun start since i have 3 aragorns.....but ifrimbazelnow u are playing against moria culture u can bid a lil higher and hope to go 1st so u can draw out RotN.......to me RotN is superb against moria....RotN plays well against sauron, isengard and nazgul culture<br>
<br>
2) trollshaw forest<br>
-card drawng capability since i play alot of possesions<br>
-its a forest....i hate it when those cantea, witchking and attea drops by to say hello at this site. 1 AVR and its bedtime for the nazguls<br>
<br>
3) council courtyard<br>
-time to boost your fellowship with fresh supplies from rivendell<br>
- minus 2 twilight <br>
<br>
4) mithril mine<br>
-draws my scimitar ( if i had any in my discard ) <br>
<br>
5) bridge of khazad dum<br>
-no choice<br>
-play the balrog if u see no armor and lots of archers in the fellowship<br>
<br>
6) lorien woods<br>
-use thrors map if u are in the lead. u get to stop moria players from playing dimrill dale<br>
-its another forest <br>
<br>
7) silverlode banks<br>
-doesn discard allies<br>
-doesn skip archery phrase<br>
-decks without rangers must exert<br>
<br>
8) shores of nen hithoel<br>
-suits a moria swarm deck<br>
<br>
9) tol brandir<br>
-its a river site<br>
-better than slopes or summit<br>
<br>
free ppl strategy<br>
----------------------<br>
i play two copies of most of my possesions ( xcept aragorns bow ....i have only 1 ) incase of any crazee discarding deck.. the xtra cards becomes dead cards which can be discarded through gwemegil or TAC....<br>
try to get your thrors map b4 site 7 and bring out silverlode banks<br>
most ppl tell me asfaloth is a waste of space and discards at underground sites.........ok.......but i play 2 asfaloths. Play 1 b4 underground site and play the other after site 5.......having aragorn str 13, boromir str 10 ( last alliance ) and arwen str 10 can really make a difference....<br>
Sorry no blade of gondor :~(     ....traded it off for hate<br>
<br>
handling uruks<br>
--------------------<br>
if u notice......my deck emphasize on AVR rite ? so what happens when somebody throw in spies of saruman ? spies is a condition and a condition is played during shadow phrase. i can easily discard the spies with secret sentinel during maneuver phrase ( b4 archery :] ).....<br>
if i can&#39;t AVR than i m sure aragorn and boromir with armor can handle the situation. My KIE can heal boromir after taking a wound from each  skirmish. usually they won&#39;t have enough twilight to drop enough minions to inflict serious damage. elrond is the only sucker which gives away 4 twilight...... <br>
<br>
handling moria<br>
------------------<br>
i hate moria........again use secret sentinel to kill of all their main condition.......moria sucks without condition  and to think that secret sentinel can remove two conditions here :) . use greenleaf and aragorns bow to take out their archers then leave the small ones for arwens bow ( which never seem to help ) .make RotN defender +1 and make him block 2 scrawnies ( my term for goblins ). usually aragorn will  beat 2 scrawnies with his sword and last alliance.if he doesn ?? big deal, two wounds then ( ouch !! ). the rest would just be a push over.<br>
always STING your opponent<br>
<br>
handling sauron<br>
------------------<br>
secret sentinel comes to the rescue again......orc bowmen and under the watching eye dies here. things can get pretty nasty if he/she plays memory of many things and shadows reach ( discards elrond and last alliance ) if he plays orc scout he/she can cancels your AVR ( same goes for uruk scout of isengard ). just try not to exhaust your companions ( HATE !!! ). All the same .......sauron won&#39;t do well without its conditions. Hmmmm maybe RotN fits better here....<br>
always STING your opponent<br>
<br>
handling nazguls<br>
---------------------<br>
nazguls ??? they can&#39;t do much against me.  Serious !!! arwen can be str 13 when skirmishing a nazgul. they can probably only afford a single nazgul b4 site 5.......even normal archery would take out a nazgul....if it doesn,  exert aragorn twice for xtra archery wounds. ford of bruinen is just another river site where i can AVR.  My only fear is relentless charge. try to choke the twilight as much as possible.........<br>
<br>
shadow strategy<br>
---------------------<br>
i play moria simply for the reason of cycling my hand faster. <br>
The most important thing is to get your goblin swarm, TAC and goblin armory out fast...... use host of a thousand to get back the fallen scavengers.....the trick is out number your opponents so that u can reinforce another scrawny in a skirmish......just make sure u can win the skirmish so u can stack them back at goblin swarm......when u recycle the scimitar, dun play it on your scavenger.....it&#39;ll just end up being shot at. play it on your scouts...( if they have archer, they have elves,  greenleaf especially ) make all your minions str 8 or 7 and make sure u outnumber him......each time u stack scrawnies on goblin swarm, your chances of outnumbering gets bigger, then eventually overwhelm him.<br>
twilight would not be a problem as runners provide additional 1 and goblin armory adds twilight and as u know my deck is about scimitar recycling..........goblin warrior comes in handy if u encounter greatest kingdom or a archery deck that revolves shoulder to shoulder and dwarven allies.<br>
